    public class Main {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            String timeString = &quot;01:43:56&quot;;
    
            LocalTime localTime = LocalTime.parse(timeString, DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(&quot;HH:mm:ss&quot;));
            System.out.println(localTime); // Output: 01:43:56
        }
    }

You have only time in the string. You can parse it to `LocalTime`; or `LocalTimeDate` but additionally you have to set a required day, e.g. today.
